cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

The paper deals with generalisation error bounds for deep learning, specifically for convolutional neural networks. This falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper's focus on convolutional neural networks and their generalisation properties makes cs.CV the most likely category, followed by cs.LG and cs.AI. The use of norm-based bounds and weight sharing also suggests a potential connection to cs.NE and cs.DS.
